We all know the most famous bit of ancient advice inscribed on the Temple of Apollo at Delphi: Know thyself.
But there remain many articles of Delphic wisdom that we would do well to keep in mind as we navigate our days.
Ask yourself: what is it to be noble, or to take the high road, or to follow the greater wisdom?
But they are good advice for parents: teach your little ones to behave themselves, and teach your older ones self-discipline.
The fact that the great majority of maxims on the list can still serve us today is itself worth further reflection.